        "subject": "LU-19929 build: Disable strict errors for RISC-V initially",
        "message": "LU-19929 build: Disable strict errors for RISC-V initially\n\nDisable strict compiler error flags for RISC-V during initial\nporting phase to allow identification of architecture-specific\nissues without blocking compilation.\n\nOnce the RISC-V port is stable and tested, this can be reverted\nto enable strict error checking like other architectures.\n\nSigned-off-by: Abdul Halim <abdul.halim@openchip.com>\nChange-Id: Ie849fc16b4d8ebddfa96d2afb777b03e01cad857\n"
      },
